  the sleep questionnaire application. The agent systematically navigated
  through the application, testing the questionnaire flow, form validation, and
  report generation. It confirmed that features like conditional fields and PDF
  generation were working as expected. The agent also tested the admin login
  functionality, verifying proper error handling for incorrect credentials, and
  interacted with various API endpoints using  to ensure data submission
  and retrieval were functioning correctly. During this process, the agent
  identified minor issues such as ESLint/TypeScript warnings in the codebase and
  an outdated page title. It concluded by providing a detailed summary of its
  findings, including both successfully working features and areas needing
  attention, along with recommendations for improvement. The user then
  instructed the agent to proceed with fixing these identified issues.
